        <section>
            <h5>Reading Response</h5>
            <h6>
                <a href="http://blog.8thlight.com/doug-bradbury/2009/08/22/why-software-development-is-a-craft.html">PROGRAMMING IS NOT A CRAFT</a>
            </h6>
            <p>Programming is acraft in my opinion because it is all about design and deals with the user's interaction with the computer. Everything is about being creative and thinking of new ideas that will make the users' lives comfortable. Software Engineering is not dead. It is just that it takes time to think of a problem and make sure it is solved in the best way possible. Making a web for example, it takes time to build, but once it is completely finished, the users will hopefully be happy to use them. Overall, the coding, the design, the creativeness, and the ideas must be creative in order for the programming and software engineering work.</p>
        </section>
    </article>

